    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 8, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 The Robot Brain You Can Actually Download Now\n\nPhysical Intelligence released the weights and code for π0 and π0-FAST to the public this week — and NVIDIA dropped its own physical AI stack the same day. It's National Robotics Week. The gift this year is a generalist robot policy that trains 5x faster than anything before it.\n\n- **The release:** PI open-sourced π0 and π0-FAST, an autoregressive model with a new robot action tokenizer that cuts training time by 80%. NVIDIA simultaneously released Cosmos and GR00T open models for robot learning and reasoning, plus Isaac Lab-Arena for robot evaluation.\n- **The ecosystem:** Boston Dynamics, Caterpillar, Franka Robotics, LG Electronics, and NEURA Robotics all unveiled new robots built on NVIDIA's stack at the same moment. That is not a coincidence.\n\n*National Robotics Week: the one week a year when \"open-source robot brain\" sounds like a normal sentence.*\n\n**Sources:** [The Robot Report](https://www.therobotreport.com/agibot-world-2026-dataset-open-source-accelerate-embodied-ai-development/) | [NVIDIA Newsroom](https://nvidianews.nvidia.com/news/nvidia-releases-new-physical-ai-models-as-global-partners-unveil-next-generation-robots) | [Physical Intelligence](https://www.pi.website/)\n\n---\n\n## 💼 Oracle Laid Off 30,000 People to Pay for Its AI Pivot\n\nLegacy enterprise is in full clearance mode. Oracle cut up to 30,000 employees, making April the worst tech layoff month of 2026 so far.\n\n- **The scale:** 85,000+ tech workers have lost jobs since January 2026. Oracle leads this round at ~30,000. Dell and Intel already made significant cuts earlier in the year. Block automated 70–80% of customer support inquiries with AI — those roles are not coming back.\n- **The pattern:** Every company cutting is a legacy enterprise firm funding an AI infrastructure buildout. Every company hiring aggressively is AI-native: Anthropic, OpenAI, xAI. The capital is moving. The humans are not.\n\n*The AI revolution is being built on the ruins of the IT department.*\n\n**Sources:** [Barchart](https://www.barchart.com/story/news/1166695/dell-announced-major-ai-driven-layoffs-in-march-2026-what-comes-next-for-dividend-paying-dell-stock) | [eWeek](https://www.eweek.com/news/more-tech-layoffs-ai-job-impact-2026/) | [Medium](https://medium.com/ai-analytics-diaries/the-uncomfortable-truth-behind-oracles-massive-30-000-layoffs-and-ai-spending-spree-e7b05c6ccdea)\n\n---\n\n## 💸 OpenAI Has a Plan for the Economy. It Involves Robot Taxes.\n\nOpenAI released a policy document this week on how governments should respond to the intelligence age: public wealth funds, taxes on robots, and a four-day workweek. The company disrupting the labor market would also like to manage the disruption.\n\n- **The proposals:** Sovereign AI wealth funds seeded by AI-generated tax revenue. Robot taxes to fund displaced worker retraining. Shorter workweeks as productivity gains compound. The mechanisms proposed are left-wing; the AI deployment model is very much not.\n- **The framing:** OpenAI explicitly describes these as ways to share \"AI's economic gains broadly.\" The company making $25 billion a year in annualized revenue is worried about inequality. Both of these things are true.\n\n*\"We're disrupting the labor market\" and \"here's our plan for the labor market\" — same document, same authors. Multitasking.*\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/06/openais-vision-for-the-ai-economy-public-wealth-funds-robot-taxes-and-a-four-day-work-week/)\n\n---\n\n## 📦 China's AGIBOT Dropped the Largest Open-Source Embodied AI Dataset\n\nAGIBOT released AGIBOT WORLD 2026 — a massive open-source dataset designed to push embodied AI research forward on five key fronts simultaneously.\n\n- **The dataset:** High-quality annotated real-world robot data covering manipulation, navigation, and multi-agent interaction. Designed for heterogeneous robot systems — any robot, any manufacturer can train on it.\n- **The context:** Open-sourcing massive embodied AI datasets has become the new competitive flex. Physical Intelligence did it with π0 the same week. The race to build generalist robot policies is also a race to build the training infrastructure first — and China is not sitting it out.\n\n*\"The model weights are available for download\" is the new \"the factory is open for business.\"*\n\n**Sources:** [The Robot Report](https://www.therobotreport.com/agibot-world-2026-dataset-open-source-accelerate-embodied-ai-development/)"
